Signals
===================================

Tutorial\script
-----------------------------------
Spawn in a Sine generator, and a cable

Drag components by clicking and holding their red parts.
Connect the generator to the ¿Dëvicé?

Match the signal, and flip the switch

If you need more room:
You can zoom in and out with the mouse wheel, or Q and E.
Dragging the middle mouse button or WASD can pan the camera.

Well done, you completed the prepared puzzles in [time].
You can proceed with randomly generated puzzles, which should all be solveable.

[Keep a running track in top right corner of puzzles solved and time taken.]

Todo
-----------------------------------
make UI with drag-droppable elements
make trashcan for removing unwanted elements

Limit mouse movement, give camera bounds

Stretch
-----------------------------------
make signal splitter/duplicator

Concept
-----------------------------------
link waveform generators and modulators to output
gens:
    sine, square, triangle
    dials: amp, freq, phase
           for tri, AoA
combiners:
    additive, multiplicative, inverter

Social
-----------------------------------
do zactronics style scores
if random endless challenges, export\import

Visuals
-----------------------------------
do green oscilio stuff
shader if we get time

have cables to plug into\out of generators and modifiers

drag the gens\mods around. Give them physics if time.

do masking on the drawn waveforms
    do glow\afterglow

Sounds
-----------------------------------
try to play the dynamically generated waveforms using Heaps

randomly generated tones\keys for waveforms, have it match their colours

generate all freq\amp\phase combos using numpy, use heaps to combine them